BEGIN_PGML
Last month, a full tank of gas for a car you drive cost you [`\$40.00\text{.}`] You hear on the news that gas prices have risen by [`12\%\text{.}`] By how much, in dollars, has the cost of a full tank gone up?

A full tank of gas now costs [_]{$cost}{10} more than it did last month.

END_PGML

############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
Let [`x`] represent the amount of increase. We can set up and solve the equation:

[```\newcommand{\pinover}[2]{\overset{\overset{\mathrm{\ #2\ }}{|}}{\strut #1 \strut}}\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\pinover{0.12}{12\%}\pinover{\cdot}{of}\pinover{40}{old\ cost}\amp\pinover{=}{is}\pinover{x}{how\ much}\\
4.8\amp=x
\end{aligned}
```]

A full tank now costs [`\$4.80`] more than it did last month.

END_PGML_SOLUTION

